Three kids aged twelve, four and three were found burned beyond recognition inside a car at Bosplaas West, North of Pretoria on Tuesday. An unknown eye-witness noticed a burned vehicle and bodies in the bushes and informed the police. According to police, the kids were reported kidnapped by their 30-year old mother the night before they were found dead. She said her boyfriend had taken the kids while she was not around and threatened to kill them. While looking for the 40-year old boyfriend, the police found him hanged inside his RDP house in Mathibestad. The motive of the killing is still unknown and a murder case has been opened at Temba police station. The bodies of the children have since been taken toÂ undergo forensic tests. -TNA Reporter